        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 26 at 8:22PM EDT by NWS Grand Rapids MI</headline>
        <description>At 822 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 6 miles southeast of Rockford to near Saranac
to 8 miles southwest of Carson City. These storms were nearly
stationary.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Grand Rapids...        Ionia...               Portland...
Wyoming...             Kentwood...            East Grand Rapids...
Grand Ledge...         Rockford...            Lowell...
Lake Odessa...         Caledonia...           Saranac...
Gerald R. Ford Inter...Ada...                 Grattan...
Fowler...              Sebewa...              Westphalia...
Lyons...               Muir...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
